{
  "intro": {
    "title": "Irregular Verbs",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Regular and irregular",
        "content": "**Regular** verbs add **-ed** for the past:\n• work → work**ed**, play → play**ed**\n\n**Irregular** verbs have special forms. You must learn them:\n• go → **went**\n• see → **saw**\n• make → **made**"
      },
      {
        "title": "Common irregular verbs",
        "content": "• go → went\n• see → saw\n• make → made\n• write → wrote\n• speak → spoke\n• take → took\n• come → came\n• get → got\n• have → had\n• do → did"
      },
      {
        "title": "Do not add -ed",
        "content": "Wrong: he **goed**, she **speaked**, I **writed**\n\nRight: he **went**, she **spoke**, I **wrote**\n\nSee Reference → Irregular verbs for a full list."
      }
    ]
  },
  "check": {
